React 0.13 adds support for ES6 class syntax alongside `React.createClass`. Developers can now write:

```js
class MyComponent extends React.Component {
  render() { return <div>{this.props.name}</div>; }
}
```

This aligns React with the direction of JavaScript itself and reduces the gap between React-specific APIs and standard language features — a pattern [[v16.8 — Hooks|Hooks will later invert]] by moving state back out of classes entirely.
